AWKA – A speeding Honda Accord driver on Friday died when he rammed into a heavy duty vehicle trying to dodge heaps of construction sand and gravel on the road at Awkuzu Oyi local government area of Anambra State. The FRSC’s First Informa­tion Report on the incident as compiled by the Ag. Sec­tor Public Education Officer, Margret Onabe, and released to journalists on Saturday read, “A Fatal Road traffic crash occurred at Obinaetiti Akwuzu, Janu­ary 21, 2022. Rep Commends Akeredolu’s Commitment To Security In Ondo UAMC Holds 80th Annual Conference At about 19:30hours. The crash was between two vehi­cles; an unidentified driver of a blue Mercedes 911 with reg­istration number: XA129AWK and unidentified driver of a Honda Accord with registra­tion number: RBX155PC. The probable cause of the fatal crash was attributed to obstruction and excessive speed. According to an eyewitness account, the Mercedes 911 driver sighted sand and grav­el in his front being used by a construction company, slowed down, while the Honda driver following behind on speed did not watch and rammed into the 911 and crashed. Three male adults were in­volved in the crash, and one male adult died (the Honda driver), while two male adults were rescued unhurt. As at the time of filing this report, the dead victim was deposited at Wisdom Mortu­ary, Awkuzu. The truck was taken to FRSC base, Nteje. Ef­fort was made by the rescue team to clear the obstruction.” POLL The Sector Commander, Anambra State Corps, Com­mander Adeoye Irelewuyi, commiserated with the family of the dead victim.